Charles G. Gabrielson, Respondent v. Frederic Waydell, et al., Appellant. Decided October 10, 1891. Exceptions by defendants directed to be heard in the first instance at general term upon verdict in plaintiff’s favor. N. B. Hoxie, for defendants. George P. Gordel, for plaintiff.

Before Dugro and Gildersleeve, JJ.

Opinion by Dugro, J.; Gildersleeve, J., concurred.

Exceptions overruled and judgment directed for plaintiff upon the verdict.
